    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-05T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-05T11:00:00-05:00" n="325"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d325">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 EW/9–544: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-05T19:00:00+03:00"
                            >September 5, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 5—2:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3321. Molotov has just given Clark Kerr and myself copy of a note which he is
                    handing the Bulgarian Minister<note n="59" xml:id="d325fn59">Ivan
                        Stamenov.</note> at 7 p.m. Moscow time in which the Soviet Government breaks
                    all relations and declares herself from now on in a state of war with Bulgaria.
                    Moscow radio will announce at 9 p.m. Details follow.<note n="60"
                        xml:id="d325fn60">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
